Package com.rubynaxela.kyanite.util

Class Vec2iIterable

java.lang.Object
com.rubynaxela.kyanite.util.Vec2iIterable
All Implemented Interfaces:
Iterable<Vector2i>
public class Vec2iIterable extends Object implements Iterable<Vector2i>
An Iterable of integer 2D coordinates. Useful for iterating over images or coordinate-based scenes. Example usage: 
Vec2iIterable.rectangle(1, 1, 16, 3).forEach((x, y) -> world.spawn(new Knight(), x, y));
The behavior of the above code will be the same as the following:
 for (int i = 1; i < 17; i++) {
     for (int j = 1; j < 4; j++) {
         world.spawn(new Knight(), i, j);
     }
 }
Note that for a non-positive rows or columns number, calling any terminal operations on this object or its iterator will have no effect.
